<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Radio&action=edit&section=31.php.html" title="Edit section: Technical">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Technical">Technical</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ntia.doc.gov/files/ntia/publications/spectrum_wall_chart_aug2011.pdf">Radio Frequency Chart</a> <a href="National_Telecommunications_and_Information_Administration" title="National Telecommunications and Information Administration">National Telecommunications and Information Administration</a> (NTIA).</li>
<li>IAteacher: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.iateacher.com/Lesson%206/L6P1-Title.htm">Interactive Explanation of Radio Receiver Construction</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://electronics.howstuffworks.com/radio.htm">How Stuff Works - Radio</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.allstar.fiu.edu/aero/VOR.htm">VOR Basic Information</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://home.comcast.net/~phils_radio_designs/">Dr. Phil's Receiver Designs</a> Single-Triode and Single-Transistor Regenerative Radio Designs</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.eetimes.com/design/microwave-rf-design/4228582/How-to-design-a-traditional-radio?Ecosystem=microwave-rf-design">How to design a traditional radio</a> by Natalian Zhai, Silicon Labs</li>
</ul>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Radio&action=edit&section=32.php.html" title="Edit section: DX">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="DX">DX</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.bdxc.org.uk">The British DX Club</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.worldofradio.com/">World of Radio</a> <a href="Glenn_Hauser" title="Glenn Hauser">Glenn Hauser</a>'s internationally known <a href="DXing" title="DXing">DX</a> radio show</li>
</ul>
